<H2>
<A name="misc">Miscellaneous</A>
</H2>

<UL>


    <li> <h3><a name="disabilities">Students with Disabilities or Special Needs</a></h3>
    <p>Any student who feels that he or she may need academic accomidations in order to meet the
      requirements of this course, as outlined in the syllabus, due to the presence of a disability, 
      should contact the Student Success Center.  Please call the office at 314-977-8885 or email them at poussonj@slu.edu to discuss the process and your options.  Confidentiality will be observed in all cases.</p>
    </li>



    <li><h3><a name="tutoring">Tutoring</a></h3>

      <P>
      Our department employees many junior/senior computer science
      majors to help out in our department labs.  Those students are
      also available to provide assistance with course materials at
      such times.
      </P>

      <P>
      Our department web page maintains a
      <a href="http://mathcs.slu.edu/Dept/labhours.html">current list of the available times and locations</a>.
      </P>

      <P>
      As stated in the <A href="#integrity">Academic Integrity</A> policy,
      these workers are an acceptable resource for help, yet
      you should still document both the source of the help as well as
      the extent, if significant.
      </P>

    </li>



  </LI>

</UL>


